 Pre Security Hardening Implementation 
Overview
After identifying and exploiting critical vulnerabilities in the Windows 11 target system, this phase focuses on implementing security hardening measures to remediate the discovered weaknesses and establish a robust security posture.
Pre-Hardening Security State
Identified Vulnerabilities

Critical: Weak password policy (password123)
Critical: Windows Defender real-time protection disabled
Critical: Windows Firewall completely disabled
High: Excessive administrative privileges
High: Unnecessary network services exposed
Medium: SMB legacy protocols enabled

Attack Vectors Successfully Exploited

SSH credential attacks
RDP credential attacks
Administrative privilege escalation
Network service enumeration
